docs.abstract: The on-demand delivery company aims to reach every ZIP code in America before its competitors.
docs.snippet: The on-demand delivery company aims to reach every ZIP code in America before its competitors.
docs.lead_paragraph: The food delivery wars are here, and the weapon of choice is money. DoorDash, an on-demand delivery app, raised a fresh $400 million from venture capital investors, the start-up said Thursday.

headline.main: $400 Million Bet on DoorDash Heats Up Delivery Wars
headline.print_headline: $400 Million in New Cash Is Delivered to DoorDash

docs.abstract: The start-up, which lets people create virtual “pin boards,” officially joined the herd of tech companies stampeding to the public markets this year by unveiling its offering prospectus.

docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Pinterest is preparing for its debut on Wall Street with a claim that few other “unicorn” start-ups can make: It is not a financial sinkhole.

headline.main: Pinterest Is Rare ‘Unicorn’ Preparing an I.P.O. Without Hemorrhaging Cash
headline.print_headline: Pinterest, on I.P.O. Path, Is Big. Its Losses Aren’t.

docs.abstract: In a newly unsealed court transcript, a former Goldman banker who pleaded guilty to money laundering called some of his actions “very much in line” with the firm’s culture.

docs.lead_paragraph: A former Goldman Sachs banker who helped orchestrate the looting of a multibillion-dollar Malaysian government investment fund told a federal judge that several other employees of the prestigious Wall Street firm had also been involved, according to a court filing unsealed Friday.

headline.main: Ex-Goldman Sachs Banker Said Colleagues Were Involved in 1MDB Scandal
